    {
      "id": "803b167a222a9248f99793e3053ee798c83a29e3",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 251,
        "name": "Bob Glossman",
        "email": "bob.glossman@intel.com",
        "username": "bogl",
        "inactive": true
      },
      "date": "2014-08-06 15:01:15.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 4: Code-Review-1\n\nDon't see why this change has a dependency on http://review.whamcloud.com/#/c/11244. They seem entirely independent to me.\n\nWhile I trust your comment about change not needed for el7, what about SLES? Do we need to be concerned about sles11sp3 or sles12?",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 4
    },
    {
      "id": "3c47c8c9e3946d2ea27f06d56dcf013c8b3f735b",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 251,
        "name": "Bob Glossman",
        "email": "bob.glossman@intel.com",
        "username": "bogl",
        "inactive": true
      },
      "date": "2014-08-06 15:31:56.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 4:\n\n(1 comment)",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 4
    },
    {
      "id": "4c336c1debda5e5594289be92637a0747e80c82c",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 141,
        "name": "Li Wei",
        "email": "wei.g.li@intel.com",
        "username": "liwei",
        "inactive": true
      },
      "date": "2014-08-07 01:49:51.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 4:\n\n(1 comment)\n\nBob, there's no landing dependency between this and 11244.  However, both issues occurred in my same lab session.  I need a build that contains both fixes in order to keep going.\n\nI don't use SLES.  Perhaps a separated patch for SLES is not that unreasonable, is it?",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 4
    },
    {
      "id": "770a2786cb5a1a0a36c6cbd129d78515a55c61a5",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 251,
        "name": "Bob Glossman",
        "email": "bob.glossman@intel.com",
        "username": "bogl",
        "inactive": true
      },
      "date": "2014-08-07 13:36:39.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 4: Code-Review+1\n\n(1 comment)\n\nCurrent commit makes it appear there is a landing dependency.  Even if you need a build with both mods I don't think it's a good idea to push the fix this way as it gives the wrong message.\n\nI think it's OK to have another patch for SLES if it's necessary.  I just don't think it's OK to forget about SLES and only fix the problem in el6.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 4
    },
    {
      "id": "4ef7c6ed3bcaa5f5cb7e478712aa3bb4e3fe3082",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 141,
        "name": "Li Wei",
        "email": "wei.g.li@intel.com",
        "username": "liwei",
        "inactive": true
      },
      "date": "2014-08-08 01:33:32.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 4:\n\nThanks, Bob.  Let me leave a note about SLES on the Jira ticket.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 4
    },
